# {{.Feature}}/stores/pgx

The {{.Feature}} feature's PostgreSQL store adapter — its own module, so a host
that brings a different datastore never pulls pgx into its graph. The dialect
sibling of `{{.Feature}}/stores/turso`: same surface, same migration version set.

- `Repositories(db)` returns a `{{.Feature}}.Repositories` after probing the
  `{{.Agg}}` table (boot-time; errors if the `{{.Source}}` migration source was
  not applied).
- `ExportMigrations(dst)` copies the canonical SQL into a host's migration dir
  (scaffold-and-own — the host applies it pre-boot).
- `MigrationsFS` / `MigrationsDir` expose the embedded schema for a host runner.

Conformance (`storetest.Run`) is env-gated (plain, no build tag):

```
docker run --rm -d -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres postgres:17
POSTGRES_TEST_DSN='postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/postgres?sslmode=disable' go test ./...
```

Without `POSTGRES_TEST_DSN` it skips loudly. `TestExportMigrations` runs
hermetically on plain `go test ./...`.
